EC2-3 (SonarQube Server)
1. Install Docker
sudo yum update -y
sudo yum install docker -y
sudo systemctl enable docker
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo usermod -aG docker ec2-user
Log out and log back in.
2. Verify Docker
docker --version
docker ps
3. Create Docker Network
docker network create sonarnet
4. Run PostgreSQL Container
docker run -d \
--name postgres \
--network sonarnet \
-e POSTGRES_USER=sonar \
-e POSTGRES_PASSWORD=sonar123 \
-e POSTGRES_DB=sonar \
-v postgres_data:/var/lib/postgresql/data \
postgres:15
Verify:
docker ps
5. Run SonarQube Container
docker run -d \
--name sonarqube \
--network sonarnet \
-p 9000:9000 \
-e SONAR_JDBC_URL=jdbc:postgresql://postgres:5432/sonar \
-e SONAR_JDBC_USERNAME=sonar \
-e SONAR_JDBC_PASSWORD=sonar123 \
-v sonarqube_data:/opt/sonarqube/data \
-v sonarqube_extensions:/opt/sonarqube/extensions \
sonarqube:lts-community
6. Verify
docker ps
7. Access SonarQube
http://<EC2-3-Public-IP>:9000
Default login:
Username: admin
Password: admin
8. Security Group
Allow inbound:
TCP 9000 → Your IP (or as needed)
That's all.
 
Once SonarQube is running on EC2-3, the Jenkins agent does not connect directly. The Jenkins server initiates the SonarQube analysis and the scanner (running on the agent) sends the report to the SonarQube server.
Architecture:
Developer
    |
GitHub
    |
Jenkins Master
    |
Jenkins Agent (Sonar Scanner)
    |
    | HTTP (Port 9000)
    |
SonarQube Server (EC2-3)
Steps
Install SonarScanner on the Jenkins Agent (EC2-2)
In SonarQube (EC2-3):
Login as admin
Go to Administration → Security → Users → Tokens
Generate a token
In Jenkins Master:
Manage Jenkins → Plugins
Install SonarQube Scanner plugin.
Manage Jenkins → System
Add a SonarQube server:
Name: SonarQube
Server URL: http://<EC2-3-private-ip>:9000
Authentication Token: Add the token as a Jenkins credential.
Manage Jenkins → Tools
Configure SonarScanner.
In your Jenkins pipeline:
withSonarQubeEnv('SonarQube') {
    sh 'sonar-scanner'
}
or for a Maven project:
withSonarQubeEnv('SonarQube') {
    sh 'mvn sonar:sonar'
}
Important
EC2-2 (Agent) must be able to reach EC2-3:9000.
In AWS, allow port 9000 in the SonarQube EC2 security group from the Jenkins EC2 security group (or the Jenkins agent's private IP).
 
